<item>
            <title>[LU-16667] Linux 6.3 client support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16667</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;New struct mnt_idmap wraps user namespace struct and changes several inode_operations functions (getattr, setattr ...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;New header &amp;lt;linux/filelock.h&amp;gt; and also breaks locks_lock_file_wait() test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;struct kernel_cap_t changed from any array of u32s to a single u64 breaking several lustre apis.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Continue using the lower 32 bits to maintain compatibility:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As of linux commit v3.6-10973-g607ca46e97a1 lustre implicitly&lt;br/&gt;
started to ignore some capabilities, see: include/uapi/linux/capability.h&lt;br/&gt;
Last capability flag was added in linux commit v5.8-rc5-1-g124ea650d307&lt;br/&gt;
The capabilities the Lustre ignores are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_MAC_OVERRIDE&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_MAC_ADMIN&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_SYSLOG&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_WAKE_ALARM&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_BLOCK_SUSPEND&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_AUDIT_READ&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_PERFMON&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_BPF&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CAP_CHECKPOINT_RESTORE&lt;br/&gt;
 None of which appear to be important to Lustre operations and should&lt;br/&gt;
 be fine to continue ignore.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
